exercise1.sp >>

NMOS & PMOS

iD_f = 51 μA
iD_i = 50.4 μA
vDS_f = 4.5 V
vDS_i = 1.5 V
ID = 50.2 μA
λ = 0.005
∆iD/∆vDS = (iD_f-iD_i)/(vDS_f-vDS_i) = 0.2 μA/V = 1/(0.2 μA/V) = 5 MΩ
∆iD/∆vDS = 1/(λ*ID) = 3.98 MΩ

ro _ 5 MΩ ≈ 3.98 MΩ (22.7% difference)

W = 10μm and L = 1μm and λ = 0.005V(-1)
iD_f = 511.2 μA
iD_i = 503.4 μA
vDS_f = 4.5 V
vDS_i = 1.5 V
ID = 501.7 μA
∆iD/∆vDS = (iD_f-iD_i)/(vDS_f-vDS_i) = 2.9 μA/V = 1/(2.9 μA/V) = 386.65 kΩ
∆iD/∆vDS = 1/(λ*ID) = 398.63 kΩ

ro _ 386.65 kΩ ≈ 398.63 kΩ (3.1% difference)

W = 1μm and L = 1μm and λ = 0.1V(-1)
iD_f = 72.4 μA
iD_i = 57.4 μA
vDS_f = 4.5 V
vDS_i = 1.5 V
ID = 54.9 μA
∆iD/∆vDS = (iD_f-iD_i)/(vDS_f-vDS_i) = 5.0 μA/V = 1/(5.0 μA/V) = 200 kΩ
∆iD/∆vDS = 1/(λ*ID) = 182.13 kΩ

ro _ 200 kΩ ≈ 182.13 kΩ (9.4% difference)

